atDirectives.description:
You can generate responsive variants of your own classes by wrapping their definitions in the `@responsive` directive:
```css
@responsive {
  .alert {
    background-color: #E53E3E;
  }
}
```

The `@screen` directive allows you to create media queries that reference your breakpoints by **name** instead of duplicating their values in your own CSS:
```css
@screen sm {
  /* ... */
}
```
…gets transformed into this:
```css
@media (min-width: 640px) {
  /* ... */
}
```

Generate `hover`, `focus`, `active` and other **variants** of your own utilities by wrapping their definitions in the `@variants` directive:
```css
@variants hover, focus {
   .btn-brand {
    background-color: #3182CE;
  }
}
```

Use the `@plugin` directive to load Tailwind CSS plugins in v4. This replaces the plugins array in the config file:
```css
@plugin "@tailwindcss/typography";
@plugin "tailwindcss-animate";
```

Use the `@custom-variant` directive to create custom variants in Tailwind CSS v4:
```css
@custom-variant dark (&:is(.dark *));
```

Use the `@theme` directive to define your design tokens in Tailwind CSS v4:
```css
@theme {
  --color-primary: #3b82f6;
  --font-sans: Inter, sans-serif;
}
```

Use the `@utility` directive to create custom utilities in Tailwind CSS v4:
```css
@utility container {
  margin-inline: auto;
  padding-inline: 2rem;
}
```
